<subSubSection id="C33817ADFFF88434E68AFEEC6E6AFF18" box="[151,311,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E68AFEEC6E6AFF18" blockId="2.[151,535,151,214]" box="[151,311,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E682FEEC6E58FF1B" box="[159,261,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Figs 1−5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E70FFEEC6E72FF18" box="[274,303,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 17−19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,637,661]" captionTargetBox="[180,1412,204,598]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[151,1436,181,613]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17−19. Sternites 7 and 8 of the new species of Glabellula, ventral view. 17, G. catiapatiuae sp. nov.; 18, G. rafaelae sp. nov.; 19, G. sarahae sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405098/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">17</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33817ADFFF88434E68AFF546C2AFE8C" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E68AFF546C2AFE8C" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E68AFF546E4FFED0" bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E751FF536E29FED0" box="[332,372,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">cua</emphasis>
at wing margin closed; mesonotum, scutellum, tergites and femora entirely dark brown, without yellow areas; female sternite 7 with lateral digitiform projections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33817ADFFF88434E6DAFF1C6B2BFE44" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E6DAFF1C6B2BFE44" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E6DAFF1C6E13FEA8" bold="true" box="[199,334,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronymic tribute to the late Dr. Catia Antunes de Mello-Patiu (MNRJ) for her great contribution to the knowledge of the diversity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C223FA5FFF88434E552FF386CFEFE44" box="[847,931,367,393]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
in South America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33817ADFFF88434E6DAFFC46DE4F9E0" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E6DAFFC46E88FA0F" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E6DAFFC46D79FE60" bold="true" box="[199,548,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
Description. 
<typeStatus id="5499FA84FFF88434E77CFFC46E93FE60" box="[353,462,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Holotype</typeStatus>
female
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E428FFC46D2AFE60" box="[565,631,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity id="4CDAE9C3FFF88434E536FFC46CCEFE63" box="[811,915,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.54" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" unit="mm" value="1.54">1.54 mm</quantity>
; wing length: 
<quantity id="4CDAE9C3FFF88434E228FFC46BC0FE63" box="[1077,1181,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E2B5FFC46BB5FE60" bold="true" box="[1192,1256,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black; eyes separated at vertex by approximately 1.25X distance between posterior ocelli; ocellar triangle shiny, ocelli yellow to dark yellow; frons dark brown, yellow in ventral and lateral margin, shiny, slightly depressed medially, with small yellow setae laterally; face yellow, with brown mark medially, slightly projecting beyond eye in lateral view; proboscis light brown to brown, smaller than head length; oral cavity and margin yellow; postcranium subshiny to shiny; setae whitish yellow; antenna brown to dark brown, yellowish pruinose; scape minute; pedicel oval; first flagellomere elliptical, about 1.5X longer than width; second flagellomere very small, about one-half width of first one; stylus absent. 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E4A5FCD86C4CFD64" bold="true" box="[696,785,655,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E53CFCD86C3AFD64" box="[801,871,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum and scutellum dark brown to black, subshiny to shiny, covered with whitish yellow setae; yellow markings on: postpronotal lobe, postalar callus and thin line along transverse suture; pleura dark brown to black, shiny, with yellow markings on: proepimeron; anterior and dorsal narrow margin of anepisternum, dorsal margin of katepisternum and dorsal 1/3 of meron. 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E338FCAC6A00FCD8" bold="true" box="[1317,1373,763,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E372FCAC6FF9FCF4" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Dark brown to black; femora with distal extremity dark yellow; tibiae with proximal and distal extremity dark yellow; tarsi dark yellow, last tarsomere darker. 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E4AFFD146DAEFC90" bold="true" box="[690,755,835,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E51EFD146C15FC90" box="[771,840,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Hyaline; costal vein, radial veins and crossvein 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E369FD136AC1FC90" box="[1396,1436,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">r-m</emphasis>
light brown, remainder veins pale yellow to translucid; costal vein ending at 1/3 distance between veins 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E322FD3F6A36FC45" box="[1343,1387,872,904]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
R 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E34DFD2D6A36FC45" attach="left" box="[1360,1387,890,904]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">4+5</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E68AFDDB6FEAFC61" box="[151,183,908,940]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
M 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E6B2FDC96FEAFC61" attach="right" box="[175,183,926,940]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
; vein 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E71FFDDC6E41FC68" box="[258,284,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Sc</emphasis>
incomplete, ending at level of 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E495FDDB6DF9FC68" box="[648,676,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Rs</emphasis>
origin; 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E51FFDDB6C43FC68" box="[770,798,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Rs</emphasis>
evanescent at connection with 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E297FDDB6BF9FC61" box="[1162,1188,908,940]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
R 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E281FDC96BF9FC61" attach="right" box="[1180,1188,926,940]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E2A8FDDB6BBFFC61" box="[1205,1250,908,940]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
R 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E2DBFDC96BBFFC61" attach="left" box="[1222,1250,926,940]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">4+5</subScript>
</emphasis>
slightly curved, ending near end of 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E76BFDE76EC8FC1D" box="[374,405,944,976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
M 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E790FD956EC8FC1D" attach="left" box="[397,405,962,976]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E7BBFDE76E98FC1D" box="[422,453,944,976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
M 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E7A0FD956E98FC1D" attach="left" box="[445,453,962,976]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
slightly curved toward wing margin; 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E56BFDE76CC8FC1D" box="[886,917,944,976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
M 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E590FD956CC8FC1D" attach="left" box="[909,917,962,976]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E5D2FDE76CB2FC1D" box="[975,1007,944,976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
M 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E5FAFD956CB2FC1D" attach="left" box="[999,1007,962,976]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">4</subScript>
</emphasis>
straight to wing margin; 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E30FFDE76A19FC07" box="[1298,1348,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">CuP</emphasis>
joining 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E68AFD846F94FC20" box="[151,201,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">CuA</emphasis>
at wing margin; 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E79AFD846EFCFC39" box="[391,417,979,1012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
A 
<subScript id="17A64663FFF88434E784FDB16EFCFC39" attach="left" box="[409,417,998,1012]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
evanescent towards wing margin; cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E548FD836C20FC20" box="[853,893,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">cua</emphasis>
closed at wing margin. Halter with stem yellow, slightly brownish infuscate, knob yellow with dark brown marks. 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E59CFDA06CABFBDC" bold="true" box="[897,1014,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E21BFDA06B10FBDC" box="[1030,1101,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Dark brown to black, shiny, covered with yellowish setae uniform in length; sternite 7 (
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E537FA4C6C26FBF8" box="[810,891,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 17−19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,637,661]" captionTargetBox="[180,1412,204,598]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[151,1436,181,613]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17−19. Sternites 7 and 8 of the new species of Glabellula, ventral view. 17, G. catiapatiuae sp. nov.; 18, G. rafaelae sp. nov.; 19, G. sarahae sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405098/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin irregular, posterior margin with lateral digitiform projection and shallow concavity medially, setae uniform in length, slightly longer distally; sternite 8 (
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E70CFA346E3EFBB0" box="[273,355,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 17−19" captionStartId="8.[151,264,637,661]" captionTargetBox="[180,1412,204,598]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[151,1436,181,613]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17−19. Sternites 7 and 8 of the new species of Glabellula, ventral view. 17, G. catiapatiuae sp. nov.; 18, G. rafaelae sp. nov.; 19, G. sarahae sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405098/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) reduced, sub-trapezoidal, with deep concave indentation medially placed on posterior margin. 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E68AFAD06E47FB6C" bold="true" box="[151,282,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E737FAD06E31FB6F" box="[298,364,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,202,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[175,1412,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−5. Glabellula catiapatiuae sp. nov., female, holotype. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, abdomen, dorsal view; 3, thorax, dorsal view; 4, left wing, ventral view; 5, terminalia, holotype. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Genital fork V-shaped, anterior margin arched with small conical projection, posterior margin bifurcate, inner arms convergent with central circular orifice, outer arms divergent, longer and tapered toward apex. Common duct short, about 1/4 length of spermatheca, basal plate hyaline; proximal spermathecal duct reduced or absent; sperm pump tubular-shaped with apical sclerotized collars well developed and formed by two level structure complex, proximally surrounded by membranous fringe and distally by well sclerotized horseshoe-shaped fold; amorphous membranous extroversion arise from sclerotized collars apex; distal spermathecal duct very long and thin, 5.5X longer than sperm pump, with elliptical swelling near base of spermatheca, swelling surrounded by minute, tangled, glandular trichomes; spermatheca as long as sperm pump, sclerotized in distal 1/3, brown, with glandular trichomes at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E6DAFB9C6ED5FA28" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1834]" box="[199,392,1483,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E6DAFB9C6E56FA28" bold="true" box="[199,267,1483,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E6DAFBB86DE4F9E0" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E6DAFBB86E8EF9C4" bold="true" box="[199,467,1519,1545]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Geographical records.</emphasis>
This species is known only from the type-locality, which is inserted in the Cerrado biome of the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49E68AC4FFF88434E799F8446EA5F9E0" box="[388,504,1555,1581]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33504B6FFF88434E419F8446D15F9E0" box="[516,584,1555,1581]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="131958A3FFF88434E445F8446DF1F9E0" box="[600,684,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1536,1560]" captionTargetBox="[178,1417,745,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-63@8.[151,1436,722,1512]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 20. Geographical records of new species of Glabellula known from Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405100/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
