<paragraph id="8B9D4426FFF88434E6DAF8F46B65F8E4" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E6DAF8F46E5BF970" bold="true" box="[199,262,1699,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Note.</emphasis>
Closed cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E78DF8F36EE5F970" box="[400,440,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">cua</emphasis>
at the wing margin in 
<taxonomicName id="4C223FA5FFF88434E4AEF8F36C3CF970" authority="Mendes &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira &amp; Lamas, 2022" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira &amp; Lamas" authorityYear="2022" box="[691,865,1700,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Glabellula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catiapatiuae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E4AEF8F36C3CF970" box="[691,865,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">G. catiapatiuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E575F8F46C9CF970" bold="true" box="[872,961,1699,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A265254FFFF88434E575F8F46C9CF970" box="[872,961,1699,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is uncommon and unique among the other species found in 
<collectingCountry id="F33504B6FFF88434E741F8906EFEF92C" box="[348,419,1735,1761]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in which cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E44DF89F6D25F92C" box="[592,632,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">cua</emphasis>
is always widely opened. Since this new species is known from only a single female specimen, future investigations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C223FA5FFF88434E4FCF8BB6CCEF8C8" authority="Mendes &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira &amp; Lamas, 2022" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Evenhuis &amp; Limeira-De-Oliveira &amp; Lamas" authorityYear="2022" box="[737,915,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Glabellula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catiapatiuae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E4FCF8BB6CCEF8C8" box="[737,915,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">G. catiapatiuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E580F8BC6CA7F8C8" bold="true" box="[925,1018,1771,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A265254FFFF88434E580F8BC6CA7F8C8" box="[925,1018,1771,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
samples are necessary to determine whether the closed cell 
<emphasis id="B9569834FFF88434E7BDF9476E95F8E4" box="[416,456,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="207">cua</emphasis>
is truly a diagnostic feature or just individual variation.
</paragraph>
